So, Coven first. We know for a fact there is a Puppetmaster since there are 2 Puppets. Puppetmaster is probably still alive, unless the Puppets happen to have been killed either by lynches or during the night around the same time. We haven't seen puppet votes have an effect, even when we've been super close number-wise, so there's a chance at least one puppet is dead, if not both. Alex and Jack spoke on D2 so Ben can't have been PM.

We also know there is a Djinn, since Lexie and I have been swapped. If they're still alive, they've either stopped swapping or are messing the the GY, which would imply a Witch too, prepping for a revive, since it doesn't look like we have a GD. Witch might explain the extra death N2, but it seems unlikely as I don't know why they'd use it so early. Preston's self-visit is either a self-protect, or he's an Alchemist (I don't believe Shaman can self-protect).

We haven't seen any evidence of a Furie yet, but that could be we haven't been lynching the correct Coven members. I don't believe we have Undead due to there being no Zombie and having no revives in this game so far, though it's possible.

In terms of killing faction, I think we have one, but the 2 deaths N2 might mean I'm wrong. If there's wolves, that could be explained by an Alphawolf, who either used it randomly or a Bloodhound told them what Alex or Jack was and they wanted them dead. If we have wolves, I think it's likely that there's a Direwolf too. I don't think there'd be a 4th, but it's possible.

Having a VM could explain no death N1 (recruit), but the second death N2 becomes a problem. We're pretty sure it wasn't Huntsman due to Teddy's block (which I assume is true, even if they are a Direwolf), but I suppose it could have been a failed ML recruit on someone else (which would also work for wolves).

I don't think both wolves and VM is likely due to the lack of deaths, though it's possible that the VM is just laying low after recruiting. There's also the possibility that Leah is indeed a Maplewolf, but the other death N2 is still a problem and they've also killed way too often for a Maplewolf if that's the case.
Sorry for the brain-dump, but I don't have a clear "it must be this" in my head
